INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('307', '1', '2010-03-16 12:21:28', '2010-03-16 12:21:28', '[column width=\"50%\" padding=\"3%\"] \r\nOur friendly, professional staff can offer expert advice at all stages of a criminal investigation to ensure the best possible outcome is achieved for you.  We are able to assist at the Police Station and Court in relation to all criminal offences, including advice on road traffic offences.\r\n\r\nWe recognise that if you or a family member has been arrested for, or charged with a criminal offence it can be an extremely difficult and stressful time.  Our staff will help to reduce the uncertainty and confusion that can arise by offering prompt and professional advice thereby ensuring that you are aware of the nature and consequences of any charges that may be brought and the process involved in dealing with your case.  Our efforts will be focused on achieving the best possible result for you.  We will ensure that your case is dealt with confidentially.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with or summonsed for  a road traffic offence it is extremely important that you seek legal advice promptly as a disqualification or penalty points can have a  significant  impact on you,  your family and your job.\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0\"] \r\nOur staff have extensive experience in criminal defence and are able to offer you specialist and practical advice in dealing with your case.  Our combination of Police Station Representatives, Solicitors and Solicitor Advocates means that your case can be dealt with in- house at all levels of the Criminal Justice System, from the Police Station to the Court of Appeal.\r\n\r\nMany clients and potential clients are concerned about costs.  Most areas of work that we cover can be funded through Legal Aid.  If we represent you a the Police Station we will not charge you at all as our costs are met by the Legal Services Commission.  If your case goes to Court we will be able to assist you in making an application for Legal Aid to cover your defence costs.\r\n\r\nOur offices are conveniently situated in the town center, close to the Police Station and Courts in both Guildford and Woking.  We are within walking distance of the railway station in both locations and on street metered parking is available.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n', 'Welcome to The Castle Partnership Solicitors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-14', '', '', '2010-03-16 12:21:28', '2010-03-16 12:21:28', '', '18', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/18-revision-14/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('2', '1', '2010-02-04 16:46:01', '2010-02-04 16:46:01', '[column width=\"50%\" padding=\"3%\"]\r\n\r\nThe three current partners formed the Castle Partnership in 2001.  Our aim then and now is to deliver high quality professional advice to those who find themselves in trouble with the Police and Courts.  The firm holds a contract with the Legal Services Commission to provide publicly funded representation to clients at the Police Station and Court.\r\n\r\nAll of our staff specialise in criminal defence work and receive ongoing training and support.\r\n\r\nOur offices are conveniently situated in the town centre, close to the Police Station and Court in Andover, Basingstoke, Guildford and Woking. We are within walking distance of the railway station in both locations and  metered parking is available nearby.\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0\"]Our offices are open between 9.00am and 5.00 pm daily from Monday to Friday.  We can arrange appointments outside of these hours in certain circumstances and endeavour to provide a 24 hour service to those who need police station advice through our emergency out of hours number all year round.\r\n\r\nThe Castle Partnership sponsor a local schools mock trials competition each year. We are also actively involved in mentoring students from the College of Law, Guildford through their mentoring scheme.\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"John Evans - Partner\"]<a href=\"/about-us/john-evans/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"John Evans\" src=\"/images/john_evans_wide.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"Ian Wilkinson - Partner\"]<a href=\"/about-us/ian-wilkinson/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"Ian Wilkinson\" src=\"/images/ian_wilkinson_wide.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"Sinéad Willox (née McNally) - Partner\"]<a href=\"/about-us/sinead-willox/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"Sinéad Willox (neé McNally)\" src=\"/images/sinead_willox_wide.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"Tim Cosham\"]<a href=\"/about-us/tim/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"Tim Cosham\" src=\"/images/tim_cosham_wide.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"Kate Holbrook\"]<a href=\"/about-us/kate/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"Kate Holbrook\" src=\"/images/kate_holbrook_wide.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"Katie Quincey\"]<a href=\"/about-us/katie/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"Katie Quincey\" src=\"/images/katie_quincey_wide.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"230\" height=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_178\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"230\" caption=\"Eleanor Towsey\"]<a href=\"/about-us/eleanor/\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-178\" title=\"Eleanor Towsey\" src=\"/images/eleanor_to