r you have a defence and help you to present your case in Court.  If you decide to plead guilty, or are convicted at trial, we will endeavour to achieve the best possible outcome for you by putting forward your explanation.\r\n\r\nYou may face a disqualification as a result of the number of points that you have on your licence, this is sometimes referred to as “totting”.  If at any time during a three year period you have 12 or more points on your licence the Court must consider imposing a driving ban for at least 6 months unless you are able to persuade the Court that you will suffer “exceptional hardship”.  We can assist in  presenting your exceptional hardship argument to the Court.\r\n\r\nPublic Funding is sometimes, but rarely, available for Road Traffic cases.  We can advise you on whether you would qualify.  If you do not we can represent you privately and will advise you, in advance, of our fees.  We try to ensure that our fees remain reasonable and competitive.\r\n\r\nContact us \r\nGuildford:  01483 300905\r\nWoking 01483 730062\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n', 'Services - Road Traffic', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '33-revision-4', '', '', '2010-02-10 14:23:27', '2010-02-10 14:23:27', '', '33', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/33-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('70', '1', '2010-02-10 14:22:50', '2010-02-10 14:22:50', 'Our friendly, professional staff can offer expert advice at all stages of a criminal investigation to ensure the best possible outcome is achieved for you.  We are able to assist at the Police Station and Court in relation to all criminal offences, including advice on road traffic offences.\r\n\r\nWe recognise that if you or a family member has been arrested for, or charged with a criminal offence it can be an extremely difficult and stressful time.  Our staff will help to reduce the uncertainty and confusion that can arise by offering prompt and professional advice thereby ensuring that you are aware of the nature and consequences of any charges that may be brought and the process involved in dealing with your case.  Our efforts will be focused on achieving the best possible result for you.  We will ensure that your case is dealt with confidentially.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with or summonsed for  a road traffic offence it is extremely important that you seek legal advice promptly as a disqualification or penalty points can have a  significant  impact on you,  your family and your job.\r\n\r\nOur staff have extensive experience in criminal defence and are able to offer you specialist and practical advice in dealing with your case.  Our combination of Police Station Representatives, Solicitors and Solicitor Advocates means that your case can be dealt with in- house at all levels of the Criminal Justice System, from the Police Station to the Court of Appeal.\r\n\r\nMany clients and potential clients are concerned about costs.  Most areas of work that we cover can be funded through Legal Aid.  If we represent you a the Police Station we will not charge you at all as our costs are met by the Legal Services Commission.  If your case goes to Court we will be able to assist you in making an application for Legal Aid to cover your defense costs.\r\n\r\nOur offices are conveniently situated in the town centre, close to the Police Station and Courts in both Guildford and Woking.  We are within walking distance of the railway station in both locations and on street metered parking is available.\r\n', 'Welcome to The Castle Partnership Solicitors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-6', '', '', '2010-02-10 14:22:50', '2010-02-10 14:22:50', '', '18', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/18-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('72', '1', '2010-02-10 17:23:33', '2010-02-10 17:23:33', '[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"6%\"] Column 1 content goes here. [/column] [column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0\"] Co