 href=\"#\">The Solicitors Regulation Authority</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Legal Services Commission</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">Community Legal Advice</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.creativitea.co.uk\">Web design by Creativitea Design Studio</a>', 'Links', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-10', '', '', '2010-02-11 11:49:53', '2010-02-11 11:49:53', '', '7', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/7-revision-10/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('137', '1', '2010-02-11 11:50:49', '2010-02-11 11:50:49', '[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"6%\"]\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Law Society of England and Wales</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Solicitors Regulation Authority</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Legal Services Commission</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">Community Legal Advice</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.creativitea.co.uk\">Web design by Creativitea Design Studio</a>\r\n[/column]', 'Links', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-11', '', '', '2010-02-11 11:50:49', '2010-02-11 11:50:49', '', '7', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/7-revision-11/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('138', '1', '2010-02-11 11:51:27', '2010-02-11 11:51:27', '[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"6%\"]\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Law Society of England and Wales</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Solicitors Regulation Authority</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">The Legal Services Commission</a>\r\n<a href=\"#\">Community Legal Advice</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.creativitea.co.uk\">Web design by Creativitea Design Studio</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0%\"]\r\n[/column]', 'Links', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-revision-12', '', '', '2010-02-11 11:51:27', '2010-02-11 11:51:27', '', '7', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/7-revision-12/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('139', '1', '2010-02-11 11:03:01', '2010-02-11 11:03:01', '[column width=\"60%\" padding=\"6%\"] If you have been arrested or have made an arrangement to be interviewed at the Police Station we can help by attending the Police Station with you or advising you over the phone.\r\n\r\nOur advice is free of charge to you.\r\n\r\nIf you have been contacted by the Police and are going to be interviewed at a Police Station please call us and we will arrange to attend with you.  You can call us on either of our office numbers or out of office  hour on our emergency contact number,  <strong>07773 300905</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you have  been arrested and are at the Police Station you will be asked by the Police if you want a solicitor.  If you ask for us they will be able to contact us.\r\n\r\nYou will be advised at the Police Station by either a Solicitor or a trained and experienced Police Station Representative.   All our staff have considerable experience of dealing with a wide cross section of offences ranging from the relatively minor to the most serious.  We will always have your interests at heart.\r\n\r\nOur offices are just  5 minutes walking distance of Guildford and Woking Police Stations, so our attendance will not delay the procedure.  We can also reach other Police Stations in the surrounding area promptly.  If we are unable to attend personally, perhaps because you have been arrested some distance away, then we can arrange for a fully qualified agent to assist you.\r\n[/column] \r\n\r\n[column width=\"34%\" padding=\"0\"]Contact us:\r\n01483 300905 (Guildford)\r\n01483 730092 (Woking)\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Services - Police Station', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15-revision-17', '', '', '2010-02-11 11:03:01', '2010-02-11 11:03:01', '', '15', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/15-revision-17/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('140', '1', '2010-02-11 11:28:20', '2010-02-11 11:28:20', '<div class=\"left_col_60\">\r\nIf you are charged with a criminal offence, or summonsed to Court for a road traffic offence, then your case will start in the Magistrates Court.\r\n\r\nAll our solicitors specialise in criminal defence law and will be able to advise you on the best way to present your case.  Any information that we receive from you and the advice that we give to you will be treated confidentially.\r\n\r\nPublic Funding  (legal aid) is not an  automatic entitlement in the Magistrates Court.  We will be able to advise you whether your case will meet the two criteria that are needed to ensure that your defence costs are covered;  the “interests of Justice test” and the “means test”.  We can assist in completing the necessary application forms with you.\r\n\r\nIn cases where public funding is not available we will advise you in writing as soon as possible how much our fees will be.  We endeavour to ensure that our fees are reasonable and competitive.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"right_col_34\">\r\nFor more information please call or e mail us on:\r\n01483 300905 (Guildford)\r\n01483 730092 (Woking)\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;\"></p>', 'Services - Magistrates Court', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '24-revision-32', '', '', '2010-02-11 11:28:20', '2010-02-11 11:28:20', '', '24', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/24-revision-32/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('142', '1', '2010-02-10 17:50:01', '2010-02-10 17:50:01', '[column width=\"67%\" padding=\"6%\"] Whilst most cases are conclude at the Magistrates Court a large number of more serious offences are sent to the Crown Court.  Cases are dealt with at the Crown Court in preference to the Magistrates Court for a variety of reasons.  It could be that the case is too serious to be dealt with by the Magistrates, or because a particular defendant has chosen to have his or her trial before a jury.\r\n\r\nWe have considerable experience in dealing with a wide cross section of offences at the Crown Court.  Your case would be prepared by a solicitor who would be assisted by a clerk. \r\nYou will be represented in Court either by one of our in-house Solicitor Advocates or a barrister, (Counsel).\r\n\r\nWe have excellent working relationships with a number of Counsels’ Chambers .\r\n\r\nExamples of the type of offences that we  regularly deal with include; Arson, Affray, ABH, Burglary, Dangerous Driving,  Drugs Offences, Fraud, GBH, Murder, Rape and other Sexual Offences, Theft,  and Violent Disorder.\r\n\r\nMost cases in the Crown Court are eligible for Public Funding,(legal aid).  There is currently no means test in the Crown Court with the exception of a small number of Courts which are part of a pilot scheme.  We can advise you whether you would qualify.\r\n[/column] \r\n[column width=\"27%\" padding=\"0\"] Contact us:\r\nGuildford:  01483 300905\r\nWoking: 01483 730062\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Services - Crown Court', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '27-revision-10', '', '', '2010-02-10 17:50:01', '2010-02-10 17:50:01', '', '27', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/27-revision-10/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('143', '1', '2010-02-10 15:38:21', '2010-02-10 15:38:21', 'We appreciate that your driving licence is important to you.  A disqualification, or even the imposition of penalty points, can have a devastating impact on you, your family and your job.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with an offence of drink driving you will know that if you plead guilty or are found guilty following  a trial the Magistrates must impose a driving ban.  A disqualification is mandatory unless you can  establish that there are special reasons not to impose a ban.  We can advise you whether or not you have a defence, and if not whether there are special reasons which can be advanced which will persuade the Court to let you continue driving.\r\n\r\nOther offences, such as speeding, carry either a disqualification or penalty points.  If convicted, the Magistrates will decide which penalty to impose depending on the facts of your case.  We can advise you whether you have a defence and help you to present your case in Court.  If you decide to plead guilty, or are convicted at trial, we will endeavour to achieve the best possible outcome for you by putting forward your explanation.\r\n\r\nYou may face a disqualification as a result of the number of points that you have on your licence, this is sometimes referred to as “totting”.  If at any time during a three year period you have 12 or more points on your licence the Court must consider imposing a driving ban for at least 6 months unless you are able to persuade the Court that you will suffer “exceptional hardship”.  We can assist in  presenting your exceptional hardship argument to the Court.\r\n\r\nPublic Funding is sometimes, but rarely, available for Road Traffic cases.  We can advise you on whether you would qualify.  If you do not we can represent you privately and will advise you, in advance, of our fees.  We try to ensure that our fees remain reasonable and competitive.\r\n\r\nContact us \r\nGuildford:  01483 300905\r\nWoking 01483 730062\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n', 'Services - Road Traffic', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '33-revision-5', '', '', '2010-02-10 15:38:21', '2010-02-10 15:38:21', '', '33', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/33-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('144', '1', '2010-02-11 12:00:27', '2010-02-11 12:00:27', '[column width=\"60%\" padding=\"6%\"]\r\nWe appreciate that your driving licence is important to you.  A disqualification, or even the imposition of penalty points, can have a devastating impact on you, your family and your job.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with an offence of drink driving you will know that if you plead guilty or are found guilty following  a trial the Magistrates must impose a driving ban.  A disqualification is mandatory unless you can  establish that there are special reasons not to impose a ban.  We can advise you whether or not you have a defence, and if not whether there are special reasons which can be advanced which will persuade the Court to let you continue driving.\r\n\r\nOther offences, such as speeding, carry either a disqualification or penalty points.  If convicted, the Magistrates will decide which penalty to impose depending on the facts of your case.  We can advise you whether you have a defence and help you to present your case in Court.  If you decide to plead guilty, or are convicted at trial, we will endeavour to achieve the best possible outcome for you by putting forward your explanation.\r\n\r\nYou may face a disqualification as a result of the number of points that you have on your licence, this is sometimes referred to as “totting”.  If at any time during a three year period you have 12 or more points on your licence the Court must consider imposing a driving ban for at least 6 months unless you are able to persuade the Court that you will suffer “exceptional hardship”.  We can assist in  presenting your exceptional hardship argument to the Court.\r\n\r\nPublic Funding is sometimes, but rarely, available for Road Traffic cases.  We can advise you on whether you would qualify.  If you do not we can represent you privately and will advise you, in advance, of our fees.  We try to ensure that our fees remain reasonable and competitive.\r\n[/column] \r\n\r\n[column width=\"34%\" padding=\"0\"]\r\nContact us:\r\n01483 300905 (Guildford)\r\n01483 730092 (Woking)\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Services - Road Traffic', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '33-revision-6', '', '', '2010-02-11 12:00:27', '2010-02-11 12:00:27', '', '33', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/33-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('145', '1', '2010-02-10 17:39:50', '2010-02-10 17:39:50', '[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"6%\"] \r\nOur friendly, professional staff can offer expert advice at all stages of a criminal investigation to ensure the best possible outcome is achieved for you.  We are able to assist at the Police Station and Court in relation to all criminal offences, including advice on road traffic offences.\r\n\r\nWe recognise that if you or a family member has been arrested for, or charged with a criminal offence it can be an extremely difficult and stressful time.  Our staff will help to reduce the uncertainty and confusion that can arise by offering prompt and professional advice thereby ensuring that you are aware of the nature and consequences of any charges that may be brought and the process involved in dealing with your case.  Our efforts will be focused on achieving the best possible result for you.  We will ensure that your case is dealt with confidentially.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with or summonsed for  a road traffic offense it is extremely important that you seek legal advice promptly as a disqualification or penalty points can have a  significant  impact on you,  your family and your job.\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0\"] \r\nOur staff have extensive experience in criminal defence and are able to offer you specialist and practical advice in dealing with your case.  Our combination of Police Station Representatives, Solicitors and Solicitor Advocates means that your case can be dealt with in- house at all levels of the Criminal Justice System, from the Police Station to the Court of Appeal.\r\n\r\nMany clients and potential clients are concerned about costs.  Most areas of work that we cover can be funded through Legal Aid.  If we represent you a the Police Station we will not charge you at all as our costs are met by the Legal Services Commission.  If your case goes to Court we will be able to assist you in making an application for Legal Aid to cover your defense costs.\r\n\r\nOur offices are conveniently situated in the town centre, close to the Police Station and Courts in both Guildford and Woking.  We are within walking distance of the railway station in both locations and on street metered parking is available.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n', 'Welcome to The Castle Partnership Solicitors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-9', '', '', '2010-02-10 17:39:50', '2010-02-10 17:39:50', '', '18', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/18-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('146', '1', '2010-02-11 11:49:10', '2010-02-11 11:49:10', '[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"6%\"]\r\nThe three current partners formed the Castle Partnership in 2001.  Our aim then and now is to deliver high quality professional advice to those who find themselves in trouble with the police and Courts.  The firm holds a contract with the Legal Services Commission to provide publicly funded representation to clients at the Police Station and Court.\r\n\r\nAll of our staff specialise in criminal defence work and receive ongoing training and support.  \r\n\r\nOur offices are conveniently situated in the town centre, close to the Police Station and Courts in both Guildford and Woking.  We are within walking distance of the railway station in both locations and  metered parking is available nearby.\r\n[/column]\r\n[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0\"]Our offices are open between 9.00am and 5.00 pm daily from Monday to Friday.  We can arrange appointments outside of these hours in certain circumstances and  endeavour to provide a 24 hour service to those who need police station advice through our emergency out of hours number all year round.\r\n\r\nThe Castle Partnership sponsor a local schools mock trial competition each year which is held at Woking Magistrates Court and are actively involved in mentoring students from the College of Law, Guildford through their mentoring scheme.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-11', '', '', '2010-02-11 11:49:10', '2010-02-11 11:49:10', '', '2', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/2-revision-11/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('147', '1', '2010-02-11 12:23:50', '2010-02-11 12:23:50', '', 'header_logo', 'The Castle Partnership', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'header_logo', '', '', '2010-02-11 12:23:50', '2010-02-11 12:23:50', '', '0', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/header_logo.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('148', '1', '2010-02-11 13:03:10', '2010-02-11 13:03:10', '', 'footer_logo', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'footer_logo', '', '', '2010-02-11 13:03:10', '2010-02-11 13:03:10', '', '0', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/footer_logo.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0'), ('149', '1', '2010-02-11 13:32:20', '2010-02-11 13:32:20', 'In order to make this site accessible to a wide audience we have placed great emphasis on testing this site with a range of people to ensure a better experience for all users and all technologies. However we welcome any comments, suggestions or feedback you have for us so please free to <a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">contact us</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Upgrade Your Browser</strong>\r\n\r\nWe have made every effort to ensure most aspects of our site work across different platforms and browsers. However, there may be times when we have been unable to provide this level of accessibility with legacy browsers. Below is a list of suggested browsers available to download from external sites. Netscape is not listed here as it has recently been discontinued, and is no longer a supported browser platform.\r\n\r\nTo come up with our list of browsers that our site will support, we have used the Yahoo Graded Support list, as it is an up to date and reliable source of information on compatibility and popularity.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"h