 since. During that time he has been a duty solicitor for both the court and the police station. Additionally he is a solicitor advocate which allows him to represent clients in Crown Court proceedings.\n\nIan has extensive experience in handling a varied case load which has in the past included everything from minor road traffic offences to complex frauds and murders.\n\nIan also maintains a close relationship with The College Of Law and is involved in the student mentoring scheme and assists in presentations to students considering a career in public funded legal services.\n\nHe also gives regular talks to police custody sergeants concerning the role of solicitors at the police station.\n[/column]\n[end_columns]', 'Ian Wilkinson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '208-autosave', '', '', '2010-04-15 14:23:58', '2010-04-15 14:23:58', '', '208', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/208-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('190', '1', '2010-02-11 16:38:19', '2010-02-11 16:38:19', '', 'Katie', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision', '', '', '2010-02-11 16:38:19', '2010-02-11 16:38:19', '', '189', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/02/189-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('191', '1', '2010-02-11 16:38:40', '2010-02-11 16:38:40', '<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\"><img src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-186\" /></a>Katie joined the Castle Partnership in July 2009.\r\n\r\nHaving graduated with a law degree she went on to the College of Law in Guildford where she gained her LPC, ( Legal Practice Course),  taking an additional module in Public Legal Services.\r\n\r\n Katie met Sinead Willox at an employment fare whilst at the College and joined us shortly afterwards.\r\n\r\nSince then Katie has enrolled on a nationally recognis