les him to appear at the Crown Court.\r\n\r\nIn addition to his criminal workload , he also manages the Guildford office and our contract with the Legal Sevices Commission.\r\n\r\nContact John at\r\n\r\nGuildford:\r\n2  Wey Court,\r\nMary Road,\r\nGuildford,\r\nGU1 4QU\r\n\r\n01483 300905\r\n<a href=\"mailto:john@castlepartnership.co.uk\">john@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'John Evans', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-revision-21', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:24:01', '2010-04-07 10:24:01', '', '166', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/166-revision-21/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('283', '1', '2010-03-16 12:40:04', '2010-03-16 12:40:04', '<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /></a>\r\n\r\nDavid Castle\'s Profile', 'David Castle', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '206-revision-3', '', '', '2010-03-16 12:40:04', '2010-03-16 12:40:04', '', '206', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/206-revision-3/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('284', '1', '2010-03-24 17:56:22', '2010-03-24 17:56:22', '<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/ian_wilkinson_main.jpg\" alt=\"Ian Wilkinson\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />\r\n\r\nIan qualified as a solicitor in 1995 and has specialised in criminal law since. During that time he has been a duty solicitor for both the court and the police station. Additionally he is a solicitor advocate which allows him to represent clients in Crown Court proceedings.\r\n\r\nIan has a very wide range of experience having dealt with serious and complex cases matters including murders heard with at The Central Criminal Court but is equally comfortable handling road traffic offence.\r\n\r\nIan also maintains a close relationship with The College Of Law and is involved in the student mentoring scheme and assists in presentations to students considering a career in public funded legal services.\r\n\r\nHe also gives regular talks to police custody sergeants concerning the role of solicitors at the police station.', 'Ian Wilkinson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '208-revision-6', '', '', '2010-03-24 17:56:22', '2010-03-24 17:56:22', '', '208', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/208-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('285', '1', '2010-03-24 17:57:35', '2010-03-24 17:57:35', '<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/kate_holbrook_main.jpg\" alt=\"Kate Holbrook\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />\r\n\r\nHaving worked in criminal defence work for many years Kate joined the Castle Partnership in 2003 as a qualified Legal Executive.   \r\n\r\nIn 2004 she became an Accredited Police Station Representative and has since gained extensive experience in representing clients in relation to all types of offences at the Police Station.\r\n', 'Kate Holbrook', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '215-revision-6', '', '', '2010-03-24 17:57:35', '2010-03-24 17:57:35', '', '215', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/215-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('286', '1', '2010-03-24 17:58:25', '2010-03-24 17:58:25', '<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/katie_quincey_main.jpg\" alt=\"Katie Quincey\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />Katie joined the Castle Partnership in July 2009.\r\n\r\nHaving graduated with a law degree she went on to the College of Law in Guildford where she gained her LPC, ( Legal Practice Course),  taking an additional module in Public Legal Services.\r\n\r\n Katie met Sinead Willox at an employment fare whilst at the College and joined us shortly afterwards.\r\n\r\nSince then Katie has enrolled on a nationally recognised Police Station Accreditation Course, which she hopes to complete by February 2010.  \r\n\r\nKatie is based at the Guildford office and her role involves assisting on the preparation of cases for Court and advising at the police station.\r\n', 'Katie Quincey', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision-6', '', '', '2010-03-24 17:58:25', '2010-03-24 17:58:25', '', '189', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/189-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('287', '1', '2010-03-24 17:21:28', '2010-03-24 17:21:28', '<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\"><img src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-186\" /></a>\r\n\r\nLance Whiteford graduated from Kingston University in 2000 and was awarded an LLB(Hons) in Law. Having successfully completed the Legal Practice Course at Guildford College of Law he joined our Company in 2001 and qualified as a Solicitor in 2003. He now works as a consultant Solicitor based at the Guildford Office.  Lance has undertaken a wide range of Court advocacy at all levels, encompassing a diverse range of offences. These include sexual offences,importation of drugs, serious violent offences (up to and including murder) and a large number of road traffic offences. He is an accredited Duty solicitor and police station advisor.', 'Lance Whiteford', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '218-revision-4', '', '', '2010-03-24 17:21:28', '2010-03-24 17:21:28', '', '218', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/218-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('288', '1', '2010-03-24 18:00:19', '2010-03-24 18:00:19', '<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/tim_cosham_main.jpg\" alt=\"Tim Cosham\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />Tim joined the Castle Partnership in 2007 and spent two years working as a  trainee solicitor and Police Station Representative before qualifying as a solicitor in September 2009. Tim specialises in criminal defence work.\r\n\r\nTim’s  training has given him extensive experience in dealing with a wide cross section of offences at the Police Station and Crown Court.  In addition to his Police Station and Crown Court work he now, as a qualified solicitor, appears in the  Magistrates Court on a regular basis.\r\n\r\nTim’s application for Duty Solicitor status is pending  and he plans to apply for advocacy rights in the Crown Court in the near future.\r\n\r\nHe has a particular interest in offences relating to the supply of controlled substances. ', 'Tim Cosham', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '185-revision-6', '', '', '2010-03-24 18:00:19', '2010-03-24 18:00:19', '', '185', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/185-revision-6/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('289', '1', '2010-04-07 10:30:30', '2010-04-07 10:30:30', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/ian_wilkinson_main.jpg\" alt=\"Ian Wilkinson\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]\r\nIan qualified as a solicitor in 1995 and has specialised in criminal law since. During that time he has been a duty solicitor for both the court and the police station. Additionally he is a solicitor advocate which allows him to represent clients in Crown Court proceedings.\r\n\r\nIan has a very wide range of experience having dealt with serious and complex cases matters including murders heard with at The Central Criminal Court but is equally comfortable handling road traffic offence.\r\n\r\nIan also maintains a close relationship with The College Of Law and is involved in the student mentoring scheme and assists in presentations to students considering a career in public funded legal services.\r\n\r\nHe also gives regular talks to police custody sergeants concerning the role of solicitors at the police station.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Ian Wilkinson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '208-revision-7', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:30:30', '2010-04-07 10:30:30', '', '208', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/208-revision-7/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('290', '1', '2010-03-24 17:59:17', '2010-03-24 17:59:17', '<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/sinead_willox_main.jpg\" alt=\"Sinéad Willox (neé McNally)\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />\r\n\r\nSinéad graduated with a degree in Irish Studies and Theology in 2003.  She went on to complete the Graduate Diploma in Law and the Legal Practice Course at the College of Law in Guildford and joined the Castle Partnership in July 2005.\r\n\r\nSince then, Sinéad has completed her training contract with the firm, qualifying as a Police Station Accredited Representative in June 2006, a Solicitor in March 2008, a Duty Solicitor in November 2008 and more recently as a Higher Rights Advocate (all proceedings) in May 2009.  \r\n\r\nSinéad is currently based at our Woking office and her role involves daily advocacy at the Magistrates’ and Crown Courts.  She regularly advises clients from the Police Station through to the Crown Court on a variety of complex cases such as Rape, Sexual Assaults, Arson, Fraud, Blackmail, Drug Offences, Violent Disorder, Burglary, Assaults and Road Traffic Offences.  \r\n\r\nSinéad has a particular interest in Legal Arguments such as Abuse of Process and Exclusion of Evidence.    \r\n\r\nSinéad is currently undertaking an LLM (Masters in Law) in Employment Law with the College of Law in Guildford and aims to complete this in 2012.', 'Sinéad Willox (neé McNally)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '210-revision-9', '', '', '2010-03-24 17:59:17', '2010-03-24 17:59:17', '', '210', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/03/210-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('291', '1', '2010-04-07 10:34:28', '2010-04-07 10:34:28', '