l module in Public Legal Services.\r\n\r\n Katie met Sinead Willox at an employment fare whilst at the College and joined us shortly afterwards.\r\n\r\nSince then Katie has enrolled on a nationally recognised Police Station Accreditation Course, which she hopes to complete by February 2010.  \r\n\r\nKatie is based at the Guildford office and her role involves assisting on the preparation of cases for Court and advising at the police station.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Katie Quincey', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision-7', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:32:25', '2010-04-07 10:32:25', '', '189', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/189-revision-7/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('300', '1', '2010-04-07 10:29:25', '2010-04-07 10:29:25', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" /></a>[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]\r\nDavid Castle\'s Profile\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'David Castle', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '206-revision-4', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:29:25', '2010-04-07 10:29:25', '', '206', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/206-revision-4/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('301', '1', '2010-04-07 10:34:54', '2010-04-07 10:34:54', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/ian_wilkinson_main.jpg\" alt=\"Ian Wilkinson\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]Ian qualified as a solicitor in 1995 and has specialised in criminal law since. During that time he has been a duty solicitor for both the court and the police station. Additionally he is a solicitor advocate which allows him to represent clients in Crown Court proceedings.\r\n\r\nIan has a very wide range of experience having dealt with serious and complex cases matters including murders heard with at The Central Criminal Court but is equally comfortable handling road traffic offence.\r\n\r\nIan also maintains a close relationship with The College Of Law and is involved in the student mentoring scheme and assists in presentations to students considering a career in public funded legal services.\r\n\r\nHe also gives regular talks to police custody sergeants concerning the role of solicitors at the police station.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Ian Wilkinson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '208-revision-8', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:34:54', '2010-04-07 10:34:54', '', '208', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/208-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('302', '1', '2010-04-07 10:25:56', '2010-04-07 10:25:56', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/john_evans_main.jpg\" alt=\"John Evans\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]John qualified as a solicitor in 1987.  He has specialised in criminal defence for over 20 years and has been a Duty Solicitor for the Police Station and Magistrates Court during that time.\r\n\r\nJohn is a qualified Solicitor Advocate in the Crown Court which enables him to appear at the Crown Court.\r\n\r\nIn addition to his criminal workload , he also manages the Guildford office and our contract with the Legal Sevices Commission.\r\n\r\nContact John at\r\n\r\nGuildford:\r\n2  Wey Court,\r\nMary Road,\r\nGuildford,\r\nGU1 4QU\r\n\r\n01483 300905\r\n<a href=\"mailto:john@castlepartnership.co.uk\">john@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'John Evans', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-revision-22', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:25:56', '2010-04-07 10:25:56', '', '166', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/166-revision-22/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('303', '1', '2010-04-07 10:39:12', '2010-04-07 10:39:12', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/kate_holbrook_main.jpg\" alt=\"Kate Holbrook\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]Having worked in criminal defence work for many years Kate joined the Castle Partnership in 2003 as a qualified Legal Executive.   \r\n\r\nIn 2004 she became an Accredited Police Station Representative and has since gained extensive experience in representing clients in relation to all types of offences at the Police Station.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Kate Holbrook', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '215-revision-8', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:39:12', '2010-04-07 10:39:12', '', '215', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/215-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('304', '1', '2010-04-07 10:33:26', '2010-04-07 10:33:26', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\"><img src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/blankperson_profile.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-186\" /></a>[/columns]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]\r\nLance Whiteford graduated from Kingston University in 2000 and was awarded an LLB(Hons) in Law. Having successfully completed the Legal Practice Course at Guildford College of Law he joined our Company in 2001 and qualified as a Solicitor in 2003. He now works as a consultant Solicitor based at the Guildford Office.  Lance has undertaken a wide range of Court advocacy at all levels, encompassing a diverse range of offences. These include sexual offences,importation of drugs, serious violent offences (up to and including murder) and a large number of road traffic offences. He is an accredited Duty solicitor and police station advisor.\r\n[/columns]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Lance Whiteford', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '218-revision-5', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:33:26', '2010-04-07 10:33:26', '', '218', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/218-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('305', '1', '2010-04-07 10:40:35', '2010-04-07 10:40:35', '[column width=\"30%\" padding-right=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/sinead_willox_main.jpg\" alt=\"Sinéad Willox (neé McNally)\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding-right=\"0%\"]Sinéad graduated with a degree in Irish Studies and Theology in 2003.  She went on to complete the Graduate Diploma in Law and the Legal Practice Course at the College of Law in Guildford and joined the Castle Partnership in July 2005.\r\n\r\nSince then, Sinéad has completed her training contract with the firm, qualifying as a Police Station Accredited Representative in June 2006, a Solicitor in March 2008, a Duty Solicitor in November 2008 and more recently as a Higher Rights Advocate (all proceedings) in May 2009.  \r\n\r\nSinéad is currently based at our Woking office and her role involves daily advocacy at the Magistrates’ and Crown Courts.  She regularly advises clients from the Police Station through to the Crown Court on a variety of complex cases such as Rape, Sexual Assaults, Arson, Fraud, Blackmail, Drug Offences, Violent Disorder, Burglary, Assaults and Road Traffic Offences.  \r\n\r\nSinéad has a particular interest in Legal Arguments such as Abuse of Process and Exclusion of Evidence.    \r\n\r\nSinéad is currently undertaking an LLM (Masters in Law) in Employment Law with the College of Law in Guildford and aims to complete this in 2012.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Sinéad Willox (neé McNally)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '210-revision-13', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:40:35', '2010-04-07 10:40:35', '', '210', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/210-revision-13/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('306', '1', '2010-04-07 10:38:34', '2010-04-07 10:38:34', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/tim_cosham_main.jpg\" alt=\"Tim Cosham\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0%\"]Tim joined the Castle Partnership in 2007 and spent two years working as a  trainee solicitor and Police Station Representative before qualifying as a solicitor in September 2009. Tim specialises in criminal defence work.\r\n\r\nTim’s  training has given him extensive experience in dealing with a wide cross section of offences at the Police Station and Crown Court.  In addition to his Police Station and Crown Court work he now, as a qualified solicitor, appears in the  Magistrates Court on a regular basis.\r\n\r\nTim’s application for Duty Solicitor status is pending  and he plans to apply for advocacy rights in the Crown Court in the near future.\r\n\r\nHe has a particular interest in offences relating to the supply of controlled substances.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Tim Cosham', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '185-revision-11', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:38:34', '2010-04-07 10:38:34', '', '185', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/185-revision-11/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('308', '1', '2010-04-15 14:08:10', '2010-04-15 14:08:10', '[column width=\"50%\" padding=\"3%\"] \r\nOur friendly, professional staff can offer expert advice at all stages of a criminal investigation to ensure the best possible outcome is achieved for you.  We are able to assist at the Police Station and Court in relation to all criminal offences, including advice on road traffic offences.\r\n\r\nWe recognise that if you or a family member has been arrested for, or charged with a criminal offence it can be an extremely difficult and stressful time.  Our staff will help to reduce the uncertainty and confusion that can arise by offering prompt and professional advice thereby ensuring that you are aware of the nature and consequences of any charges that may be brought and the process involved in dealing with your case.  Our efforts will be focused on achieving the best possible result for you.  We will ensure that your case is dealt with confidentially.\r\n\r\nIf you have been charged with or summonsed for  a road traffic offence it is extremely important that you seek legal advice promptly as a disqualification or penalty points can have a  significant  impact on you,  your family and your job.\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column width=\"47%\" padding=\"0\"] \r\nOur staff have extensive experience in criminal defence and are able to offer you specialist and practical advice in dealing with your case.  Our combination of Police Station Representatives, Solicitors and Solicitor Advocates means that your case can be dealt with in- house at all levels of the Criminal Justice System, from the Police Station to the Court of Appeal.\r\n\r\nMany clients and potential clients are concerned about costs.  Most areas of work that we cover can be funded through Legal Aid.  If we represent you a the Police Station we will not charge you at all as our costs are met by the Legal Services Commission.  If your case goes to Court we will be able to assist you in making an application for Legal Aid to cover your defence costs.\r\n\r\nOur offices are conveniently situated in the town center, close to the Police Station and Courts in both Guildford and Woking.  We are within walking distance of the railway station in both locations and on street metered parking is available.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n', 'Welcome to The Castle Partnership Solicitors', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '18-revision-15', '', '', '2010-04-15 14:08:10', '2010-04-15 14:08:10', '', '18', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/18-revision-15/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('309', '1', '2010-04-15 14:17:41', '2010-04-15 14:17:41', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/katie_quincey_main.jpg\" alt=\"Katie Quincey\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0\"]Katie joined the Castle Partnership as a trainee solicitor in 2009.\n\nHaving graduated with a law degree she went on to the College of Law in Guildford where she gained her LPC, ( Legal Practice Course),  taking an additional module in Public Legal Services.\n\n Katie met Sinead Willox at an employment fare whilst at the College and joined us shortly afterwards.\n\nKatie is an accredited Police Station Representative.  \n\nKatie is based at the Guildford office and her role involves assisting on the preparation of cases for Court and advising at the police station.\n[/column]\n[end_columns]', 'Katie Quincey', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-autosave', '', '', '2010-04-15 14:17:41', '2010-04-15 14:17:41', '', '189', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/189-autosave/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('310', '1', '2010-04-07 10:41:28', '2010-04-07 10:41:28', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/katie_quincey_main.jpg\" alt=\"Katie Quincey\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0\"]Katie joined the Castle Partnership in July 2009.\r\n\r\nHaving graduated with a law degree she went on to the College of Law in Guildford where she gained her LPC, ( Legal Practice Course),  taking an additional module in Public Legal Services.\r\n\r\n Katie met Sinead Willox at an employment fare whilst at the College and joined us shortly afterwards.\r\n\r\nSince then Katie has enrolled on a nationally recognised Police Station Accreditation Course, which she hopes to complete by February 2010.  \r\n\r\nKatie is based at the Guildford office and her role involves assisting on the preparation of cases for Court and advising at the police station.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Katie Quincey', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision-8', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:41:28', '2010-04-07 10:41:28', '', '189', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/189-revision-8/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('312', '1', '2010-04-07 10:43:07', '2010-04-07 10:43:07', '[column width=\"30%\" padding=\"3%\"]<img class=\"size-full wp-image-186 alignleft\" title=\"blankperson_profile\" src=\"/images/ian_wilkinson_main.jpg\" alt=\"Ian Wilkinson\" width=\"210\" height=\"210\" />[/column]\r\n[column width=\"57%\" padding=\"0\"]Ian qualified as a solicitor in 1995 and has specialised in criminal law since. During that time he has been a duty solicitor for both the court and the police station. Additionally he is a solicitor advocate which allows him to represent clients in Crown Court proceedings.\r\n\r\nIan has a very wide range of experience having dealt with serious and complex cases matters including murders heard with at The Central Criminal Court but is equally comfortable handling road traffic offence.\r\n\r\nIan also maintains a close relationship with The College Of Law and is involved in the student mentoring scheme and assists in presentations to students considering a career in public funded legal services.\r\n\r\nHe also gives regular talks to police custody sergeants concerning the role of solicitors at the police station.\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Ian Wilkinson', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '208-revision-9', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:43:07', '2010-04-07 10:43:07', '', '208', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/208-revision-9/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('313', '1', '2010-04-07 10:00:43', '2010-04-07 10:00:43', '[column width=\"60%\" padding=\"6%\"]\r\nWhilst most cases are conclude at the Magistrates Court a large number of more serious offences are sent to the Crown Court.  Cases are dealt with at the Crown Court in preference to the Magistrates Court for a variety of reasons.  It could be that the case is too serious to be dealt with by the Magistrates, or because a particular defendant has chosen to have his or her trial before a jury.\r\n\r\nWe have considerable experience in dealing with a wide cross section of offences at the Crown Court.  Your case would be prepared by a solicitor who would be assisted by a clerk. \r\n\r\nYou will be represented in Court either by one of our in-house Solicitor Advocates or a barrister, (Counsel).\r\n\r\nWe have excellent working relationships with a number of Counsels’ Chambers.\r\n\r\nExamples of the type of offences that we  regularly deal with include; Arson, Affray, ABH, Burglary, Dangerous Driving,  Drugs Offences, Fraud, GBH, Murder, Rape and other Sexual Offences, Theft,  and Violent Disorder.\r\n\r\nMost cases in the Crown Court are eligible for Public Funding,(legal aid).  There is currently no means test in the Crown Court with the exception of a small number of Courts which are part of a pilot scheme.  We can advise you whether you would qualify.\r\n[/column] \r\n\r\n[column width=\"34%\" padding=\"0\"]\r\n<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/crowncourt1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/crowncourt1.jpg\" alt=\"crowncourt\" title=\"crowncourt\" width=\"240\" height=\"345\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-259\" /></a>\r\nContact us:\r\n01483 300905 (Guildford)\r\n01483 730092 (Woking)\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]', 'Services - Crown Court', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '27-revision-12', '', '', '2010-04-07 10:00:43', '2010-04-07 10:00:43', '', '27', 'http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/2010/04/27-revision-12/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'), ('314', '1', '2010-04-07 09:54:22', '2010-04-07 09:54:22', '[column width=\"60%\" padding=\"6%\"]\r\nIf you have been arrested or have made an arrangement to be interviewed at the Police Station we can help by attending the Police Station with you or advising you over the phone.\r\n\r\nOur advice is free of charge to you.\r\n\r\nIf you have been contacted by the Police and are going to be interviewed at a Police Station please call us and we will arrange to attend with you.  You can call us on either of our office numbers or out of office  hour on our emergency contact number,  <strong>07773 300905</strong>.\r\n\r\nIf you have  been arrested and are at the Police Station you will be asked by the Police if you want a solicitor.  If you ask for us they will be able to contact us.\r\n\r\nYou will be advised at the Police Station by either a Solicitor or a trained and experienced Police Station Representative.   All our staff have considerable experience of dealing with a wide cross section of offences ranging from the relatively minor to the most serious.  We will always have your interests at heart.\r\n\r\nOur offices are just  5 minutes walking distance of Guildford and Woking Police Stations, so our attendance will not delay the procedure.  We can also reach other Police Stations in the surrounding area promptly.  If we are unable to attend personally, perhaps because you have been arrested some distance away, then we can arrange for a fully qualified agent to assist you.\r\n[/column] \r\n\r\n[column width=\"34%\" padding=\"0\"]\r\n<a href=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/policestation1.jpg\"><img src=\"http://castle.creativitea.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2010/02/policestation1.jpg\" alt=\"policestation\" title=\"policestation\" width=\"240\" height=\"345\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-261\" /></a>\r\nContact us:\r\n01483 300905 (Guildford)\r\n01483 730092 (Woking)\r\n<a href=\"mailto:enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk\">enquiries@castlepartnership.co.uk</a>\r\n[/column]\r\n[end_columns]\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Services - Police Station', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '15